  "read": "The hidden fwd/bwd wrapper wall is the lifetime release of the original graph-bearing loss, not the detached scalar return. Explicitly deleting loss before return moves the previous 4.6-4.9s residual into the named forward_backward.drop_original_loss phase and collapses the remaining call-boundary residual to about 5 ms. This is diagnostic, not a throughput improvement: step 2 is still only 53.97 TFLOPs/GPU. The next production branch should reduce or avoid this graph-free path through FSDP/autograd/checkpoint tensor lifetime changes, not by returning a detached loss alone."
